</string>
<string name="careGuide3">

        <![CDATA[
    <h3>
        Week 3: </h3>

    <ul>
        <li>
            After cleared from surgeon begin exercise program. </li>
        <li>
            Complete exercises 5-10 repetitions 3-5x per day, as tolerated </li>
        <li>
            Range of Motion Exercises – complete all these exercises actively, with no assistance from your unaffected hand </li>
        <li>
            Tendon Gliding</li>
        <li>
            Thumb flexion, extension, opposition - AROM </li>
        <li>
            Gentle wrist flexion and extension - AROM</li>
        <li>
            Use degrees to track your progress!</li>

        <li>Desensitization: After sutures are removed and incision is cleared by doctor begin scar massage.</li>
        <li>
            Desensitization: Rub scar site during the day with different textures. </li>
        <li>
            Scar tissue management</li>
        <li>
            Scar massage </li>
        <li>
            Apply a thick lotion or cream to your scar and in a use fingers to rub firmly in a circular motion all around and on scar site. </li>
    </ul>
    ]]>
</string>
<string name="careGuide4">

    <![CDATA[
    <h3>Week 4 -6 </h3>

    <ul>
        <li>
            After cleared from surgeon begin exercise program. </li>
        <li>
            Complete exercises 5-10 repetitions 3-5x per day, as tolerated </li>
        <li>
            Range of Motion Exercises – complete all these exercises actively, with no assistance from your unaffected hand </li>
        <li>
            Tendon Gliding</li>
        <li>
            Thumb flexion, extension, opposition - AROM </li>
        <li>
            Gentle wrist flexion and extension - AROM</li>
        <li>
            Use degrees to track your progress!</li>
        <li>
            Desensitization: After sutures are removed and incision is cleared by doctor begin scar massage.</li>
        <li>
            Desensitization: Rub scar site during the day with different textures. </li>
        <li>
            Scar tissue management</li>
        <li>
            Scar massage 	</li>
        <li>
            Apply a thick lotion or cream to your scar and in a use fingers to rub firmly in a circular motion all around and on scar site. </li>
        <li>
            NEW! – Strengthening </li>
        <li>
            Complete exercises 5-10 repetitions 3-5x per day, as tolerated </li>
        <li>
            Strengthening: Squeeze rubber ball</li>
        <li>
            Strengthening: Wrist curls with 3 pound weight</li>
        <li>
            .. other wrist stuff </li>

    </ul>
    ]]>
